WEBVTT

01:05.690 --> 01:07.775
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

01:52.737 --> 01:54.404
OLESON'S GOT
A PRETTY BIG ORDER
HERE THIS TIME.

01:54.572 --> 01:57.074
WELL, TOWN'S
GROWING LIKE A WEED.
MORE PEOPLE EVERY DAY.

01:57.242 --> 01:59.034
YEAH.
MOSTLY FOREIGNERS.

01:59.202 --> 02:00.786
I'LL BET GOVERNMENT
BETTER PUT A STOP TO IT,

02:00.954 --> 02:03.330
OR THERE AIN'T GONNA BE
ANY OF US PURE AMERICANS
LEFT NO PLACE.

02:03.498 --> 02:05.499
DIDN'T KNOW YOU
WERE AN INDIAN, HORACE.

02:05.667 --> 02:07.209
- WHAT?
- NEVER MIND.

02:07.377 --> 02:08.418
WELL, DON'T TAKE
ALL DAY, FARLEY.

02:08.586 --> 02:10.003
Farley: KEEP
YOUR BRITCHES ON.

02:10.171 --> 02:12.923
I'VE GOT AN EXPENSIVE
LOAD OF FOREIGN
LIQUOR IN HERE.

02:13.091 --> 02:14.133
YOU KNOW, SCOTCH.

02:14.300 --> 02:19.721
I HAD TO DOUBLE-LOCK IT.

02:19.889 --> 02:23.308
LAND SAKE.

02:23.476 --> 02:25.185
WATCH YOURSELF, FARLEY.

02:54.048 --> 02:56.967
WELL, LAND SAKE!

02:57.135 --> 03:00.387
COME BACK HERE, YOU!

03:00.555 --> 03:02.472
GET HIM!

03:02.640 --> 03:06.685
[CHARLES AND JONATHAN LAUGHING]

03:08.688 --> 03:11.356
Horace: COME BACK HERE!

03:16.863 --> 03:20.449
HEY, YOU,
I SAID COME BACK HERE!

04:07.538 --> 04:10.499
Horace: OKAY, WE GOT HIM NOW.
LET'S SPLIT UP.

04:10.667 --> 04:12.459
[LAUGHTER]

04:13.419 --> 04:15.837
HE'S GOT TO BE
IN HERE SOMEWHERE.

04:19.717 --> 04:21.218
LET'S HAVE
A LOOK IN HERE.

04:32.730 --> 04:34.940
HEY.

04:39.195 --> 04:40.529
[LAUGHS]

04:40.697 --> 04:42.739
KIND OF A FUNNY PLACE
FOR A WHISKEY CRATE,
ISN'T IT?

04:42.907 --> 04:45.575
COME ON.

04:49.038 --> 04:51.081
TOBY NOE!

04:51.249 --> 04:52.249
SO YOU GOT HIM.

04:52.417 --> 04:53.375
Jonathan:
OH, COME ON, TOBY.

04:53.543 --> 04:54.876
NOW YOU'RE GONNA
TAKE A LICKING.

04:55.044 --> 04:56.420
NOW, HOLD ON.
THE OLD MAN'S
A FRIEND OF OURS.

04:56.587 --> 04:58.422
WELL, I DON'T CARE
WHO HE IS.
HE STOWED AWAY.

04:58.589 --> 05:00.257
HE STOLE WHISKEY.
I'M GOING
TO TAKE HIM IN.

05:00.425 --> 05:01.633
WHAT IF HE MAKES GOOD
ON THE WHISKEY?

05:01.801 --> 05:02.759
WELL...

05:02.927 --> 05:04.261
HE'S JUST AN OLD MAN.
NOW, COME ON.

05:04.429 --> 05:05.762
ALL RIGHT. $20.

05:05.930 --> 05:07.848
- $20?
- NOW PAY UP OR LET'S GO!

05:08.016 --> 05:09.266
JUST PAY HIM,
TOBY.

05:09.434 --> 05:12.519
ALL RIGHT.
I'VE ONLY GOT $10,
MY LIFE SAVINGS.

05:12.687 --> 05:13.979
I'LL TAKE IT.

05:14.147 --> 05:17.691
AND DON'T LET ME
SEE YOU ON ONE
OF MY TRAINS AGAIN.

05:20.028 --> 05:21.278
YOU WANT TO PICK UP
YOUR ORDER NOW?

05:21.446 --> 05:22.654
Charles: WE'LL BE ALONG
IN A MINUTE.

05:22.822 --> 05:27.117
AH.

05:27.285 --> 05:28.910
TOBY, WHAT ON EARTH
ARE YOU DOING AROUND HERE?

05:29.078 --> 05:30.829
OH, I'M ON MY
WAY TO FRISCO.

05:30.997 --> 05:33.749
I HEAR THAT IT'S A
GREAT GAMBLING TOWN.

05:33.916 --> 05:36.710
ONLY I GOT NOTHING
TO GAMBLE WITH NOW.

05:36.878 --> 05:39.129
JONATHAN AND I
ARE HEADING BACK
TO WALNUT GROVE TODAY.

05:39.297 --> 05:40.464
WHY DON'T YOU
COME ALONG WITH US?

05:40.631 --> 05:42.132
YOU CAN STAY AT MY
PLACE FOR A WHILE.

05:42.300 --> 05:44.801
CAROLINE AND THE KIDS
WOULD LOVE TO SEE YOU.

05:44.969 --> 05:45.886
THEY WOULD?

05:46.054 --> 05:47.179
SURE, THEY WOULD.

05:47.347 --> 05:51.141
YOU CAN DRY OUT AND GET
OFF THIS DRINKING BINGE.

05:51.309 --> 05:53.310
I COULD, COULDN'T I?
ALL RIGHT.

05:53.478 --> 05:55.479
NO MORE BOOZE!

05:55.646 --> 05:57.147
LOOK, HERE, I'LL
CARRY THAT FOR YOU.

05:57.315 --> 05:58.607
NO. NO NEED
FOR THAT.

05:58.775 --> 06:03.070
SUIT YOURSELF.
[SMASH]

06:03.237 --> 06:05.072
HA HA. TOBY.

06:14.707 --> 06:17.084
Laura: YOU KNOW THAT BOY
WHO SITS BEHIND ME
IN THE THIRD ROW?

06:17.251 --> 06:19.669
Albert: JASON BROOKS?
YEAH, I KNOW HIM.

06:19.837 --> 06:21.505
DO YOU THINK
HE LIKES ME?

06:21.672 --> 06:23.215
WHY?
DO YOU LIKE HIM?

06:23.383 --> 06:24.383
- YEAH.
- OH.

06:24.550 --> 06:26.301
SOMETIMES I THINK
HE'S STARING AT ME,

06:26.469 --> 06:29.012
BUT WHEN I TURN AROUND
TO LOOK AT HIM,
HE JUST TURNS AWAY.

06:29.180 --> 06:30.931
I DON'T KNOW IF
HE LIKES ME OR NOT.

06:31.099 --> 06:33.350
SOUNDS TO ME LIKE
HE'S PLAYING
IT REAL SMART.

06:33.518 --> 06:35.018
Laura: YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:35.186 --> 06:37.854
I THINK I'M JUST GOING
TO ASK HIM OUTRIGHT
IF HE LIKES ME.

06:38.022 --> 06:40.232
OH, THAT'S THE WORST
THING YOU CAN DO.

06:40.400 --> 06:42.234
THEN HE'LL KNOW FOR
SURE YOU LIKE HIM.

06:42.402 --> 06:44.528
SO? WHAT'S WRONG
WITH THAT?

06:44.695 --> 06:47.364
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO LET HIM KNOW
YOU LIKE HIM.

06:47.532 --> 06:49.866
UNLESS HE LETS YOU KNOW
THAT HE LIKES YOU FIRST.

06:50.034 --> 06:51.952
WELL, IF I'M WAITING
FOR HIM TO LET ME KNOW

06:52.120 --> 06:54.079
AND HE'S WAITING
FOR ME TO LET HIM KNOW,

06:54.247 --> 06:56.790
THEN WE COULD SPEND
THE REST OF OUR LIVES
NEVER KNOWING!

06:56.958 --> 06:58.417
WELL, THAT'S
THE WAY IT IS.

06:58.584 --> 07:00.001
WELL, THAT'S DUMB.

07:00.169 --> 07:02.838
IT'S NOT DUMB.

07:03.005 --> 07:04.381
IF YOU PLAY
HARD TO GET,

07:04.549 --> 07:06.925
HE'LL COME CRAWLING
ON HIS HANDS AND KNEES.

07:07.093 --> 07:09.553
BUT WHY WOULD I WANT HIM
TO DO A THING LIKE THAT?

07:09.720 --> 07:12.139
I LIKE HIM
STANDING UP.

07:12.306 --> 07:13.890
I THINK I'M JUST GOING
TO TELL HIM FLAT OUT

07:14.058 --> 07:15.392
THAT I LIKE HIM.

07:15.560 --> 07:18.854
OKAY, BUT DON'T SAY
I DIDN'T WARN YOU.

07:25.903 --> 07:28.780
I'M PRETTY SURE
SHE LIKES ME.

07:28.948 --> 07:30.407
I MEAN, SHE LOOKS
AT ME A LOT.

07:30.575 --> 07:33.201
OR MAYBE SHE
JUST CAN'T GET OVER
HOW UGLY YOU ARE.

07:33.369 --> 07:35.787
CUT IT OUT, NED,
YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE HELPING ME.

07:35.955 --> 07:38.915
ALL RIGHT, I'LL
TELL YOU WHAT
I'D DO IF I WAS YOU.

07:39.083 --> 07:41.334
THE TOWN DANCE
IS COMING UP
IN 2 WEEKS.

07:41.502 --> 07:44.754
IF I WERE YOU, I'D ASK
LAURA IF SHE WANTS TO GO.

07:44.922 --> 07:45.964
I DON'T KNOW.

07:46.132 --> 07:49.009
BUT WHAT IF
SHE SAYS NO?

07:49.177 --> 07:50.302
I MEAN, I'D JUST DIE.

07:50.470 --> 07:51.970
I COULDN'T COME
TO SCHOOL ANYMORE.

07:52.138 --> 07:54.306
JASON, YOU GOT TO GET
PAST YOUR SHYNESS.

07:54.474 --> 07:56.766
IT STOPS YOU COLD
EVERY TIME.

07:56.934 --> 07:58.143
I CAN'T HELP IT.

07:58.311 --> 08:01.188
WHENEVER I REALLY
LIKE A GIRL,

08:01.355 --> 08:03.064
THEN I GET ALL
CHOKED UP INSIDE.

08:03.232 --> 08:06.276
WELL, START CHOKING,
LOOK WHO'S COMING.

08:19.832 --> 08:25.629
JASON, THERE'S
SOMETHING I'VE BEEN
MEANING TO ASK YOU.

08:25.796 --> 08:28.673
DO YOU LIKE ME?

08:28.841 --> 08:30.717
NO.

08:39.810 --> 08:41.811
NOW, WHY DID YOU
GO OFF AND SAY THAT?

08:41.979 --> 08:44.981
I DON'T KNOW.
IT JUST CAME OUT
IS ALL.

08:45.149 --> 08:46.691
YOU'RE A DUMMY.

08:46.859 --> 08:48.944
WELL, SHE'S
NOT SUPPOSED
TO ASK ME THAT.

08:49.111 --> 08:50.695
AND WHY NOT?

08:50.863 --> 08:54.157
BECAUSE. WELL, WHAT
IF I SAID "YES"?

08:54.325 --> 08:57.160
THEN SHE COULD SAY,
"WELL, I DON'T
LIKE YOU."

08:57.328 --> 08:59.913
I TAKE IT BACK, JASON.
YOU'RE NOT A DUMMY.

09:00.081 --> 09:02.582
YOU'RE AN IDIOT.

09:07.630 --> 09:11.174
Charles: CAROLINE!

09:11.342 --> 09:13.843
OH, CHARLES.

09:14.011 --> 09:16.346
- YOU'RE BACK EARLY.
- THAT'S RIGHT.

09:16.514 --> 09:18.181
I HAVE SOME COMPANY
AT THE BACK
OF THE WAGON.

09:18.349 --> 09:21.142
WHO? TOBY!

09:21.310 --> 09:23.186
TOBY NOE.

09:23.354 --> 09:24.729
IT'S A HARD NAME
TO FORGET.

09:24.897 --> 09:27.524
[LAUGHS] WHAT ON EARTH
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

09:27.692 --> 09:30.694
WELL, I WAS, UH,
HEADING TO SAN FRANCISCO

09:30.861 --> 09:34.531
ON A SPECIAL C--CASE,
YOU M--MIGHT SAY.

09:34.699 --> 09:36.366
AND I HAVE RUN
INTO CHARLES.

09:36.534 --> 09:38.118
HE'S GOING TO SPEND A
LITTLE TIME WITH US.

09:38.286 --> 09:39.494
WONDERFUL!

09:39.662 --> 09:42.289
ALBERT WILL BE SO
HAPPY TO SEE YOU.

09:42.456 --> 09:44.499
WELL, JUST FOR A
FEW DAYS, YOU KNOW,

09:44.667 --> 09:47.210
I WOULDN'T WANT
TO BE A BOTHER.

09:47.378 --> 09:51.006
NONSENSE, YOU STAY
AS LONG AS YOU LIKE.

09:51.173 --> 09:52.507
OH, I BET YOU'RE
BOTH STARVED.

09:52.675 --> 09:54.009
I AM, WHAT
ABOUT YOU, TOBY?

09:54.176 --> 09:58.054
OH, WELL, I SUPPOSE I COULD
DO WITH A BITE OF SOMETHING.

09:58.222 --> 10:00.140
[LAUGH] THE CHILDREN
WILL BE HOME SOON,

10:00.308 --> 10:02.183
- WE'LL HAVE SUPPER EARLY.
- ALL RIGHT, GOOD.

10:02.351 --> 10:03.643
I'LL GET TOBY
TO SETTLE INSIDE.

10:03.811 --> 10:06.646
GOOD.

10:06.814 --> 10:08.064
Charles:
WHAT'S FOR SUPPER?

10:08.232 --> 10:09.274
PORK CHOPS.

10:09.442 --> 10:10.900
OOH! LOT OF THEM!

10:11.068 --> 10:14.279
THANK YOU, CHARLES.
DON'T MIND IF I DO.

10:14.447 --> 10:17.407
AH, I HAVEN'T EATEN
THIS MUCH IN YEARS.

10:17.575 --> 10:20.035
I HAVEN'T EATEN
THAT MUCH IN
AN ENTIRE YEAR.

10:20.202 --> 10:21.453
YES, WELL,
MY FATHER SAID,

10:21.621 --> 10:23.997
"A GOOD APPETITE IS ALWAYS
A COMPLIMENT TO THE COOK."

10:24.165 --> 10:25.749
I WISH YOU WOULDN'T
BE SO COMPLIMENTARY.

10:25.916 --> 10:28.418
CAN I HAVE ANOTHER
CUP OF COFFEE, CAROLINE?
IT MIGHT FILL ME UP.

10:28.586 --> 10:31.338
CERTAINLY.
I'LL PUT ON
ANOTHER POT.

10:31.505 --> 10:33.089
CARRIE, YOU BETTER
GET TO YOUR HOMEWORK.

10:33.257 --> 10:34.382
YES, MAMA.

10:34.550 --> 10:39.095
WELL, LAURA, YOU'VE
HARDLY EATEN A THING.

10:39.263 --> 10:40.472
BROKEN HEART.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.682
SHE LIKES SOMEBODY,
BUT HE DON'T LIKE HER.

10:42.850 --> 10:48.438
OH? HOW LONG HAS
THIS BEEN GOING ON?

10:48.606 --> 10:50.273
A COUPLE OF DAYS.

10:50.441 --> 10:54.694
AH, A LITTLE
HEARTBREAK, EH?

10:54.862 --> 10:56.029
YEAH, I GUESS.

10:56.197 --> 10:58.323
WELL, I KNOW EXACTLY
HOW YOU FEEL.

10:58.491 --> 11:01.785
I'VE BEEN ON
THE CHASING END OF
A FEW ROMANCES MYSELF.

11:01.952 --> 11:04.913
I'VE GOT CUPCAKES FOR
DESSERT, IF ANYBODY'S
GOT ANY ROOM.

11:05.081 --> 11:06.122
CUPCAKES!

11:06.290 --> 11:09.834
I HAVEN'T HAD CUPCAKES
FOR YEARS. HA HA!

11:13.798 --> 11:15.006
[CHUCKLES]

11:15.174 --> 11:17.676
[BELL TOLLS]

11:36.570 --> 11:38.154
Charles: NELS.

11:50.710 --> 11:51.835
Caroline: MORNING.

11:52.002 --> 11:53.795
Toby: I HAVEN'T MET
MANY REVERENDS, YOU KNOW.

11:53.963 --> 11:56.172
REVEREND, I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET A FRIEND OF
THE FAMILY, MR. TOBY NOE.

11:56.340 --> 11:58.049
WELL, I'M VERY PLEASED
TO MEET YOU, MR. NOE.

11:58.217 --> 11:59.968
LIKEWISE,
REVEREND.

12:00.136 --> 12:01.177
CHARLES, I THINK
A FEW OF US

12:01.345 --> 12:02.846
HAD BETTER HAVE
A MEETING AFTER SERVICE.

12:03.013 --> 12:05.598
WE'VE GOT TO FIND SOMEBODY
TO PLAY THAT NEW ORGAN.

12:05.766 --> 12:07.434
WELL, I THOUGHT
MRS. OLESON
VOLUNTEERED FOR THAT.

12:07.601 --> 12:08.977
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.

12:09.145 --> 12:11.396
IF SHE PLAYS IT,
WE'LL LOSE HALF
THE CONGREGATION.

12:11.564 --> 12:12.856
[LAUGHTER]

12:13.023 --> 12:17.068
WELL, TOBY CAN PLAY THE ORGAN.
HE'S A GREAT MUSICIAN.

12:17.236 --> 12:18.862
IS THAT TRUE, MR. NOE?

12:19.029 --> 12:21.156
UH, WELL, UH...

12:21.323 --> 12:24.159
SOME FOLKS THINK
I'M PRETTY GOOD.

12:24.326 --> 12:25.618
Reverend: WOULD YOU
PLAY FOR US TODAY?

12:25.786 --> 12:26.828
OH, I DON'T, UH--

12:26.996 --> 12:28.496
OH, COME ON, TOBY.
WOULD YOU?

12:28.664 --> 12:31.458
WELL, SURE.
WHY NOT?

12:31.625 --> 12:33.460
BLESS YOU, MR. NOE.

12:33.627 --> 12:35.211
I COULD USE IT.
HA HA.

12:35.379 --> 12:36.546
HE'S NOT KIDDING.

12:36.714 --> 12:38.214
[LAUGHING]

12:38.382 --> 12:41.468
[PEOPLE TALKING]

12:53.022 --> 12:57.192
THERE ARE VERY FEW
SOUNDS IN THIS WORLD

12:57.359 --> 13:02.405
AS BEAUTIFUL AS THE
SOUND OF A CHURCH ORGAN
ON A SUNDAY MORNING.

13:02.573 --> 13:06.075
SO I THINK WE ARE
VERY FORTUNATE

13:06.243 --> 13:10.622
TO HAVE A TRULY
GIFTED ORGAN PLAYER.

13:10.790 --> 13:15.126
MR. TOBY NOE WILL ACCOMPANY
US IN THE SINGING
OF THE HYMNS TODAY.

13:15.294 --> 13:17.796
MR. NOE.

13:30.518 --> 13:33.436
SHALL WE RISE?

13:35.439 --> 13:38.900
[PLAYING UPBEAT VERSION
OF SUNDAYS AFTER TRINITY]

13:47.993 --> 13:51.162
[CLAPPING]

13:57.962 --> 14:01.256
ROCK OF AGES
CLEFT FOR ME

14:01.423 --> 14:04.634
LET ME HIDE MYSELF
IN THEE

14:04.802 --> 14:08.054
LET THE WATER
AND THE BLOOD

14:08.222 --> 14:11.474
FROM THY WOUNDED SIDE
WHICH FLOWED

14:11.642 --> 14:14.644
BE OF SIN
A DOUBLE CURE

14:14.812 --> 14:18.106
SAVE FROM WRATH
AND MAKE ME PURE

14:18.274 --> 14:21.484
WHEN I DRAW
THIS FLEETING BREATH

14:21.652 --> 14:24.863
WHEN MINE EYES
SHALL CLOSE IN DEATH

14:25.030 --> 14:28.324
WHEN I RIDE
TO WORLDS UNKNOWN

14:28.492 --> 14:31.578
AND BEHOLD THEE
ON THE THRONE

14:31.745 --> 14:34.956
ROCK OF AGES,
CLEFT FOR ME

14:35.124 --> 14:38.960
LET ME HIDE MYSELF
IN THEE

14:48.762 --> 14:51.806
GOOD-BYE.

14:51.974 --> 14:55.435
SO NICE
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

14:55.603 --> 14:57.687
GOOD-BYE.

15:00.316 --> 15:01.941
- REVEREND ALDEN.
- HELLO, AMANDA.

15:02.109 --> 15:03.985
DON'T YOU
"HELLO" ME!
I'M FURIOUS.

15:04.153 --> 15:05.695
THOSE HYMNS
WERE A DISGRACE!

15:05.863 --> 15:06.821
I'M SORRY YOU
DIDN'T LIKE IT, AMANDA.

15:06.989 --> 15:08.406
I THOUGHT IT
WAS QUITE INSPIRING.

15:08.574 --> 15:10.783
INSPIRING, NOTHING.
I DO NOT COME
INTO GOD'S HOUSE

15:10.951 --> 15:12.535
TO HEAR
THE DEVIL'S MUSIC!

15:12.703 --> 15:15.455
GOOD DAY, REVEREND!

15:28.844 --> 15:33.056
REVEREND, WHO IS
THAT SPIRITED WOMAN?

15:33.223 --> 15:34.557
IT'S AMANDA COOPER.

15:34.725 --> 15:36.017
WIDOW?

15:36.185 --> 15:37.435
A SPINSTER.

15:37.603 --> 15:39.145
OH, HOW LOVELY,

15:39.313 --> 15:41.731
AN UNPICKED FLOWER.

15:41.899 --> 15:46.069
LAURA! LAURA!

15:46.236 --> 15:49.489
LAURA!

15:54.411 --> 15:55.703
BELIEVE ME, TOBY,

15:55.871 --> 15:58.206
YOU DON'T WANT
TO KNOW WHERE
AMANDA COOPER LIVES.

15:58.374 --> 15:59.749
BUT I DO.

15:59.917 --> 16:04.087
TOBY, SHE'S MEAN,
AND SHE'S SOUR.

16:04.254 --> 16:05.338
SHE'S ORNERY.

16:05.506 --> 16:07.006
AND THOSE ARE
HER GOOD POINTS.

16:07.174 --> 16:10.927
ALBERT, I'M THE TYPE
THAT LIKES TO FORM
HIS OWN OPINIONS.

16:11.095 --> 16:13.888
NOW, WHERE
DOES SHE LIVE?

16:14.056 --> 16:15.765
- SHE DOESN'T LIKE PEOPLE, TOBY.
- NO.

16:15.933 --> 16:17.475
AND SHE DOESN'T
HAVE ANY FRIENDS.

16:17.643 --> 16:19.727
THE ONLY ONE
SHE'LL TALK TO
IS HER DUMB OLD CAT.

16:19.895 --> 16:22.480
BUT WHERE
DOES SHE LIVE?

16:22.648 --> 16:26.484
OH, WHAT'S THE USE?

16:26.652 --> 16:28.569
RIGHT DOWN THERE.

16:42.126 --> 16:45.461
Amanda:
PERCY, IT'S LUNCHTIME.

16:45.629 --> 16:47.046
THERE YOU ARE.

16:47.214 --> 16:49.799
EAT UP, DARLING.

16:49.967 --> 16:52.343
OH.

16:52.511 --> 16:53.970
[SIGHS]

16:54.138 --> 16:59.600
OH, PERCY, I HAD
THE STRANGEST
DREAM LAST NIGHT.

16:59.768 --> 17:01.686
I WAS YOUNG AGAIN,

17:01.854 --> 17:06.065
AND I WAS WALKING
BY THIS BEAUTIFUL LAKE,

17:06.233 --> 17:08.651
AND IT WAS
A TERRIBLY HOT DAY,

17:08.819 --> 17:11.070
SO I TOOK OFF
ALL MY CLOTHES.

17:11.238 --> 17:13.072
WELL, THERE WAS
NOBODY AROUND.

17:13.240 --> 17:17.035
AND, UH, I JUST
JUMPED IN THE WATER,

17:17.202 --> 17:21.164
AND, LO AND BEHOLD,
THERE WAS A MAN IN THE WATER,

17:21.331 --> 17:25.626
AND HE WAS SWIMMING
RIGHT TOWARDS ME.

17:25.794 --> 17:29.338
OH, I JUST DON'T KNOW
HOW IT ALL WOULD HAVE ENDED

17:29.506 --> 17:33.217
IF YOU HADN'T JUMPED
ON THE BED AND WOKE ME UP.

17:35.721 --> 17:39.474
YOU DUMB CAT, YOU.

17:42.352 --> 17:45.271
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

17:52.446 --> 17:54.489
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

17:54.656 --> 17:56.199
HOW DO YOU DO, MA'AM?

17:56.366 --> 17:58.910
I'M TOBY NOE, AND I'D
LIKE TO APOLOGIZE

17:59.078 --> 18:00.703
FOR WHAT HAPPENED
IN CHURCH.

18:00.871 --> 18:03.831
IT WAS NOT
MY INTENTION
TO UPSET ANYONE.

18:03.999 --> 18:05.374
INTENTION OR NOT,
MR. NOE,

18:05.542 --> 18:08.878
THAT WAS NOT
PROPER CHURCH MUSIC.

18:09.046 --> 18:11.547
YES, MA'AM,
BUT, YOU SEE,

18:11.715 --> 18:13.216
HAPPY MUSIC IS
THE ONLY KIND OF MUSIC

18:13.383 --> 18:15.218
MY FINGERS
KNOW HOW TO PLAY.

18:15.385 --> 18:18.638
WELL, I ACCEPT
YOUR APOLOGY. NOW IF
YOU'LL EXCUSE ME--

18:18.806 --> 18:20.890
UH, WAIT.

18:21.058 --> 18:23.518
NOW THAT WE'VE MET,
I WONDER IF YOU WOULD
DO ME THE PLEASURE

18:23.685 --> 18:27.772
OF LETTING ME
SIT HERE WITH YOU
ON THIS VERANDA.

18:27.940 --> 18:31.442
JUST WHAT ARE
YOUR INTENTIONS,
MR. NOE?

18:31.610 --> 18:34.362
STRICTLY HONORABLE,
I ASSURE YOU.

18:34.530 --> 18:35.863
I WOULD BE LESS
THAN HONEST

18:36.031 --> 18:41.828
IF I DID NOT ADMIT
THAT I FIND YOU
VERY ATTRACTIVE.

18:41.995 --> 18:44.914
SIR, YOU ARE A CLOD!

18:45.082 --> 18:46.499
YEAH...WHAT?!

18:46.667 --> 18:48.584
A CLOD WITHOUT
DECENCY OR MANNERS.

18:48.752 --> 18:50.461
WE HAVE NOT BEEN
PROPERLY INTRODUCED!

18:50.629 --> 18:52.922
DON'T YOU CALL ME
A CLOD, SISTER!

18:53.090 --> 18:54.924
I JUST
INTRODUCED MYSELF.

18:55.092 --> 18:56.509
I AM NOT YOUR SISTER!

18:56.677 --> 18:59.053
THANK GOD FOR THAT!

18:59.221 --> 19:00.721
OF ALL THE NERVE!

19:00.889 --> 19:03.516
[DOOR SLAMS]

19:11.525 --> 19:17.572
BOY, TOBY,
SURE SWEPT HER
OFF HER FEET.

19:47.519 --> 19:50.146
I COULD KICK MYSELF.

19:50.314 --> 19:53.608
WHY DID I HAVE TO ARGUE
WITH HER LIKE THAT?

19:53.775 --> 19:55.318
BECAUSE
SHE'S MEAN,
THAT'S WHY.

19:55.485 --> 19:56.903
NO. SHE'S NOT MEAN.

19:57.070 --> 20:00.615
SHE'S FULL OF FIRE.
SHE'S ALIVE.

20:00.782 --> 20:01.991
I GOT TO FIND SOME WAY

20:02.159 --> 20:05.161
TO GET MYSELF BACK
IN HER GOOD GRACES.

20:05.329 --> 20:10.833
WELL, YOU
COULD ALWAYS
LEAVE TOWN.

20:11.001 --> 20:12.084
AHA!

20:12.252 --> 20:15.338
OH, UH, UH, LAURA,

20:15.505 --> 20:19.508
WOULD YOU, UH,
ACT AS MY GO-BETWEEN?

20:19.676 --> 20:22.094
GUESS SO.

20:22.262 --> 20:25.473
ALBERT, YOU REMEMBER
THAT PRETTY LITTLE GARDEN

20:25.641 --> 20:27.225
WE SAW BACK THERE?

20:27.392 --> 20:29.977
WOULD YOU BORROW
SOME FLOWERS FOR ME?

20:30.145 --> 20:31.187
SURE.

20:31.355 --> 20:33.189
HA HA!
LET'S GO!

20:33.357 --> 20:35.775
[GIGGLES]

20:37.486 --> 20:40.446
[KNOCK ON DOOR]
[MEOW]

20:43.367 --> 20:46.786
MISS COOPER,
THE HONORABLE TOBY NOE
WISHES TO APOLOGIZE

20:46.954 --> 20:50.539
AND ASK IF HE MAY
COME CALLING
ON THURSDAY EVENING.

20:50.707 --> 20:53.292
YOU TELL MR. NOE
THE ANSWER IS "NO"

20:53.460 --> 20:56.587
AND TELL HIM TO
STOP BOTHERING ME!

21:07.391 --> 21:10.893
I DECLARE, HE IS THE MOST
GALLING, OBSTINATE MAN

21:11.061 --> 21:13.396
I EVER MET IN MY LIFE.

21:13.563 --> 21:15.815
HE'S A BULLDOG.

21:28.245 --> 21:31.289
I DECLARE, IF HE DOESN'T
STOP PESTERING ME,

21:31.456 --> 21:37.586
I JUST MIGHT REPORT
HIM TO THE AUTHORITIES.

21:53.061 --> 21:56.522
SORRY.

22:00.360 --> 22:03.863
FORGET ABOUT IT, TOBY,
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

22:04.031 --> 22:07.033
YEAH. GIVE UP.

22:07.200 --> 22:10.453
GIVE UP? WHY
SHOULD I GIVE UP?

22:10.620 --> 22:12.705
SHE'S CRAZY ABOUT ME.

22:12.873 --> 22:16.459
SHE'S JUST
NOT AWARE OF IT YET.

22:20.964 --> 22:23.090
Albert: BOY,
HE SURE IS STUBBORN.

22:23.258 --> 22:25.259
HE SURE IS.

22:39.441 --> 22:41.067
YOU SURE YOU DON'T WANT ME
TO HEAT THAT UP FOR YOU?

22:41.234 --> 22:42.443
NO, NO,
I'M DOING FINE.

22:42.611 --> 22:45.571
I'M JUST GLAD YOU HAD
THIS HAM SLICE FOR ME.

22:45.739 --> 22:48.199
I'VE NEVER IN MY LIFE
SEEN A MAN EAT LIKE TOBY.

22:48.367 --> 22:49.575
YOU'RE TELLING ME.

22:49.743 --> 22:51.369
I'M NEVER CLOSING MY EYES
AGAIN DURING BLESSING.

22:51.536 --> 22:53.746
I SAID, "AMEN,"
OPENED MY EYES AND
THE ROAST WAS GONE.

22:53.914 --> 22:55.790
[CHUCKLES]

22:55.957 --> 22:57.541
WELL, HE NEVER
DID LIKE LEFTOVERS.

22:57.709 --> 22:59.668
AT LEAST THERE
ARE NOT LEFTOVERS.

22:59.836 --> 23:01.462
I'LL BE IN AS SOON
AS I FINISH THIS.

23:01.630 --> 23:03.714
- GOOD NIGHT.
- GOOD NIGHT.

23:07.719 --> 23:08.928
OH, CHARLES?

23:09.096 --> 23:11.013
YES.

23:11.181 --> 23:13.974
MAY I, UH, BORROW
THE WAGON TONIGHT?

23:14.142 --> 23:16.852
ANYTHING YOU
WANT, TOBY.

23:17.020 --> 23:18.396
DON'T YOU
WANT TO KNOW
WHERE I'M GOING?

23:18.563 --> 23:21.524
YOU WANT TO TELL
ME, YOU GO AHEAD
AND YOU TELL ME.

23:21.691 --> 23:25.361
TO COURT MY AMANDA.

23:25.529 --> 23:26.779
YOU DO WHAT YOU WANT.

23:26.947 --> 23:28.155
I THINK IT'S NO USE.

23:28.323 --> 23:32.034
"NO" IS A WORD
THAT IS NOT
IN MY VOCABULARY,

23:32.202 --> 23:34.120
EXCEPT FOR
MY LAST NAME. HA HA.

23:34.287 --> 23:36.163
WISH ME LUCK,
CHARLES.

23:36.331 --> 23:38.582
GOOD LUCK, TOBY.

23:46.383 --> 23:49.427
CAROLINE!

23:55.725 --> 24:00.855
Toby:   BEAUTIFUL DREAMER,
WAKE UNTO ME

24:01.022 --> 24:03.941
STARLIGHT AND DEWDROPS

24:04.109 --> 24:07.987
ARE WAITING FOR THEE

24:08.155 --> 24:11.282
SOUNDS OF THE RUDE WORLD

24:11.450 --> 24:13.742
HEARD IN THE DAY

24:13.910 --> 24:17.163
LULLED BY THE MOONLIGHT

24:17.330 --> 24:20.791
HAVE ALL PASSED AWAY

24:20.959 --> 24:23.669
BEAUTIFUL DREAMER

24:23.837 --> 24:26.881
QUEEN OF MY SONG

24:27.048 --> 24:30.134
LIST WHILE I WOO THEE

24:30.302 --> 24:33.888
WITH SWEET MELODY

24:34.055 --> 24:36.474
GONE ARE THE CARES

24:36.641 --> 24:38.851
OF LIFE'S BUSY THRONG

24:39.019 --> 24:40.686
- MR. NOE...
-   BEAUTIFUL--

24:40.854 --> 24:42.563
MR. NOE!

24:42.731 --> 24:45.816
THIS HARASSMENT
HAS GOT TO STOP.

24:45.984 --> 24:47.985
I AM NOT
HARASSING YOU.

24:48.153 --> 24:49.612
I AM COURTING YOU.

24:49.779 --> 24:52.281
WELL, I HAVE NO
WISH TO BE COURTED.

24:52.449 --> 24:55.451
NOW YOU WILL PLEASE
GET OFF MY VERANDA.

24:55.619 --> 24:57.786
BEAUTIFUL DREAMER

24:57.954 --> 25:01.040
GO HOME, YOU
EXASPERATING MAN!

25:01.208 --> 25:03.542
BEAUTIFUL DREAM--

25:03.710 --> 25:07.171
ALL RIGHT.
YOU CAN COME
TO TEA TOMORROW.

25:10.717 --> 25:14.512
[SOFTLY]
BEAUTIFUL DREAMER

25:14.679 --> 25:16.931
AWAKE WITH ME

25:17.098 --> 25:19.683
CAROLINE, HE'S JUST
DRIVING ME CRAZY.
IT'S AMANDA THIS,

25:19.851 --> 25:22.937
AMANDA THAT.
THAT'S ALL I HEAR
ABOUT IS AMANDA.

25:23.104 --> 25:24.438
OH, CHARLES.

25:24.606 --> 25:27.441
YOU KNOW
WHAT IT'S LIKE--
BEING IN LOVE.

25:27.609 --> 25:28.943
IT'S FULL
OF SUFFERING.

25:29.110 --> 25:31.487
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
SUFFERING? THE MAN
EATS LIKE A HORSE.

25:31.655 --> 25:33.656
HE DOESN'T OFFER
TO PAY FOR ANYTHING.

25:33.823 --> 25:35.324
HE JUST STAYS HERE,
AND HE EATS,
AND HE EATS.

25:35.492 --> 25:37.493
I THOUGHT HE WAS
GOING TO STAY
FOR A FEW DAYS.

25:37.661 --> 25:40.079
CHARLES, HAVE
SOME SYMPATHY.

25:40.247 --> 25:43.415
AFTER ALL,
HE'S AN OLD MAN.

25:43.583 --> 25:47.962
CAROLINE, I'M GOING
TO BE AN OLD MAN
BEFORE HE LEAVES.

25:48.129 --> 25:50.214
TRY AND GET
A GOOD NIGHT'S REST.

25:50.382 --> 25:52.841
YOU WILL FEEL
BETTER TOMORROW.

25:53.009 --> 25:54.843
ALL RIGHT.

25:55.011 --> 25:58.514
- LOVE YOU.
- GOOD NIGHT.

25:58.682 --> 26:01.267
HMM.

26:01.434 --> 26:03.852
[DOOR OPENS]
Toby: CHARLES!

26:04.020 --> 26:06.814
CHARLES, CAROLINE--
SHE INVITED ME TO TEA!

26:06.982 --> 26:09.316
TOMORROW, FOR TEA!

26:09.484 --> 26:11.569
WHY DON'T YOU
TRY TO GET
SOME REST, TOBY,

26:11.736 --> 26:12.987
SO YOU CAN LOOK
YOUR BEST?

26:13.154 --> 26:14.780
OH, I COULDN'T SLEEP.
I'M TOO EXCITED!

26:14.948 --> 26:16.907
WHEN I GET EXCITED,
I GET HUNGRY.

26:17.075 --> 26:18.826
BUT I'M SORRY, TOBY.

26:18.994 --> 26:20.452
THE ROAST
IS ALL GONE.

26:20.620 --> 26:22.079
OH, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT A THING.

26:22.247 --> 26:25.332
I STOPPED AT THE HENHOUSE
ON THE WAY IN. HEE HEE.

26:25.500 --> 26:28.711
YOU TWO GET SOME SLEEP.
I'LL COOK THEM UP MYSELF.

26:28.878 --> 26:30.212
YOU'RE TOO KIND.

26:30.380 --> 26:33.424
OH, THANK YOU.

26:39.889 --> 26:42.558
AN ACT OF KINDNESS
NEVER GOES UNPUNISHED.

26:42.726 --> 26:45.519
OH, CHARLES.

26:45.687 --> 26:50.399
Toby:
BEAUTIFUL DREAMER

26:50.567 --> 26:52.735
[LAUGHING]

26:52.902 --> 26:54.695
WAKE UNTO ME

26:54.863 --> 26:57.573
STARLIGHT
AND DEW DROPS

26:57.741 --> 27:03.287
ARE WAITING
FOR THEE

27:03.455 --> 27:04.580
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

27:04.748 --> 27:07.291
SOUNDS OF
THE RUDE WORLD

27:07.459 --> 27:10.252
ARE HEARD IN A DAY

27:17.260 --> 27:18.552
HEY, KIDS!

27:18.720 --> 27:20.596
HEY, KIDS!
HOW DO I LOOK?

27:20.764 --> 27:21.805
YOU LOOK FINE!

27:21.973 --> 27:24.183
- WISH ME LUCK.
- GOOD LUCK, TOBY.

27:24.351 --> 27:25.309
HAVE FUN.

27:25.477 --> 27:29.438
I HOPE TO.
I HOPE TO.
HA HA HA.

27:29.606 --> 27:34.026
LOOK AT HIM.
HE'S WALKING ON AIR.

27:34.194 --> 27:37.196
WOULD YOU EVER BELIEVE
THAT FOLKS THAT OLD
WOULD FALL IN LOVE?

27:37.364 --> 27:40.324
NEVER. ALBERT,
DO YOU THINK

27:40.492 --> 27:43.410
THEY'RE ACTUALLY
GOING TO KISS
EACH OTHER?

27:43.578 --> 27:44.953
I DON'T KNOW,

27:45.121 --> 27:47.665
BUT I'D SURE
LIKE TO SEE IT
IF THEY DO.

27:47.832 --> 27:51.210
LET'S CUT ACROSS
McMURPHY'S PLACE
SO HE WON'T SEE US.

27:51.378 --> 27:53.671
- RIGHT.
- LET'S GO.

28:04.974 --> 28:08.602
UH, JUST WHAT LINE
OF WORK ARE YOU
IN, MR. NOE?

28:08.770 --> 28:09.895
I'M RETIRED.

28:10.063 --> 28:12.606
REALLY?
RETIRED FROM WHAT?

28:12.774 --> 28:14.983
A LITTLE BIT OF THIS,
A LITTLE BIT OF THAT.

28:15.151 --> 28:17.778
YOU ARE ELUSIVE,
MR. NOE.

28:17.946 --> 28:19.071
NOT REALLY.

28:19.239 --> 28:20.489
I'VE NEVER
THOUGHT IT PROPER
FOR A PERSON

28:20.657 --> 28:24.076
TO BRAG ABOUT
HIS FINANCIAL EXPLOITS.

28:24.244 --> 28:26.829
BESIDES, I'D RATHER
HEAR ABOUT YOU.

28:26.996 --> 28:29.665
WELL, THERE'S REALLY
NOT TOO MUCH TO TELL.

28:29.833 --> 28:32.710
I WAS, UH, RAISED
IN LOUISIANA,

28:32.877 --> 28:38.257
AND, UH, THEN I'VE
LIVED HERE THE REST
OF MY LIFE.

28:38.425 --> 28:39.883
UH, WOULD YOU
LIKE SOME MORE TEA?

28:40.051 --> 28:43.178
NO, THANK YOU.
IT WAS REALLY DELICIOUS.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

28:43.346 --> 28:47.891
OH, I NOTICED THAT
YOU HAD A PIANO,
MISS COOPER.

28:48.059 --> 28:49.518
DO YOU MIND
IF I SEE IT?

28:49.686 --> 28:52.312
IF YOU LIKE.

28:56.025 --> 29:01.697
[PLAYING NOTES SLOWLY]

29:01.865 --> 29:03.365
BEAUTIFUL TONE,

29:03.533 --> 29:07.536
AND I HAVE
JUST THE SONG FOR
A PRETTY SOUTHERN GIRL.

29:07.704 --> 29:10.414
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

29:10.582 --> 29:14.835
[PLAYING CAMPTOWN RACES]

29:16.880 --> 29:20.758
OH, I LOVE THAT SONG!

29:53.875 --> 29:56.126
[BARKING]

29:56.294 --> 29:57.669
[MEOWING]

29:57.837 --> 29:59.922
LORD!

30:00.089 --> 30:01.924
BANDIT! BANDIT!
COME HERE! BANDIT!

30:02.091 --> 30:04.092
Amanda: YOU KNOW
THAT DOG! THAT'S
YOUR DOG, ISN'T IT?

30:04.260 --> 30:05.928
[GLASS BREAKING]
Toby: IT IS NOT MY DOG!

30:06.095 --> 30:07.179
IT'S THE DOG
OF A FRIEND OF MINE.

30:07.347 --> 30:09.097
OUT! GET OUT OF MY
HOUSE THIS MINUTE!

30:09.265 --> 30:11.058
PLEASE, PLEASE!
IT'S NOT MY DOG!

30:11.226 --> 30:13.602
OUT! YES, YOU.
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE!

30:13.770 --> 30:15.479
- NOW I MEAN IT!
- I LIKE CATS!

30:15.647 --> 30:19.233
OUT! OUT! OUT
AND STAY OUT!

30:29.452 --> 30:31.954
WE'RE SORRY, TOBY.

30:32.121 --> 30:35.582
PLEASE FORGIVE US.

30:35.750 --> 30:40.587
YEAH. WE DIDN'T
MEAN TO RUIN IT
FOR YOU. I SWEAR.

30:40.755 --> 30:43.465
OH, IT...

30:43.633 --> 30:46.468
IT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY DIFFERENCE.

30:46.636 --> 30:50.556
WHY DO I KEEP
KNOCKING MY HEAD
AGAINST THE WALL?

30:50.723 --> 30:54.351
I THINK
IT BEST THAT I
JUST LEAVE TOWN.

31:23.089 --> 31:24.214
[CHUCKLES]

31:24.382 --> 31:27.301
WELL, YOU CERTAINLY
WERE IN A GOOD
MOOD TONIGHT.

31:27.468 --> 31:29.678
WELL, OF COURSE
I WAS IN A GOOD MOOD.

31:29.846 --> 31:32.347
YOU HEARD TOBY.
HE'S GOING TO LEAVE.

31:32.515 --> 31:34.725
I FEEL SORRY FOR HIM.

31:34.893 --> 31:37.686
WELL, SO WILL I
AFTER HE'S GONE.

31:37.854 --> 31:39.855
AND LET'S FACE IT,
HIS MISERY DIDN'T
HURT HIS APPETITE.

31:40.023 --> 31:42.274
HE MADE THAT ROAST
LOOK LIKE A CHOP.

31:42.442 --> 31:44.067
I KNOW, BUT--

31:44.235 --> 31:45.986
[THUD]

31:46.154 --> 31:49.531
[SHUFFLING FOOTSTEPS]

31:52.702 --> 31:56.038
CHARLES?

31:56.205 --> 31:57.414
YES, TOBY?

31:57.582 --> 31:59.166
I COULDN'T SLEEP.

31:59.334 --> 32:00.876
I THOUGHT IF I HAD
SOMETHING TO EAT

32:01.044 --> 32:04.046
IT'D MAKE ME DROWSY.

32:04.213 --> 32:06.048
THERE'S
NOTHING LEFT.

32:06.215 --> 32:10.010
WELL, MAYBE SOME RAW ONIONS
AND A LITTLE MILK.

32:10.178 --> 32:14.264
I THINK THAT OUGHT
TO DO THE TRICK.

32:14.432 --> 32:17.893
THAT SOUNDS VERY
RELAXING, TOBY.

32:18.061 --> 32:20.228
I HOPE I DIDN'T
DISTURB YOU.

32:20.396 --> 32:22.397
OH, NO.
NO, THAT'S FINE.

32:22.565 --> 32:26.068
YEAH, A LITTLE RAW ONION
AND HOT MILK, AND I'LL BE FINE.

32:32.283 --> 32:36.620
RAW ONIONS
AND HOT MILK?

32:36.788 --> 32:42.000
[BOTH LAUGHING]

32:42.168 --> 32:46.004
I JUST DON'T
BELIEVE IT.

33:08.319 --> 33:10.362
YOU KNOW WHAT
WE GOT TO DO?

33:10.530 --> 33:12.906
WHAT?

33:13.074 --> 33:16.034
WE GOT TO HELP TOBY
MARRY THAT OLD PRUNE.

33:16.202 --> 33:18.620
MARRY HER? WHY?

33:18.788 --> 33:20.080
WELL, THAT'S
THE ONLY WAY

33:20.248 --> 33:22.290
WE'RE GOING TO GET HIM
TO STAY IN WALNUT GROVE.

33:22.458 --> 33:23.625
SHE WON'T MARRY HIM.

33:23.793 --> 33:26.420
SHE WON'T EVEN
TALK TO HIM ANYMORE.

33:26.587 --> 33:28.505
WELL,
WE COULD FIX THAT.

33:28.673 --> 33:31.633
YEAH. WE COULD
TAKE THE BLAME
FOR WHAT BANDIT DID.

33:31.801 --> 33:35.512
NO. THAT
WOULDN'T DO IT.

33:35.680 --> 33:37.472
[SIGHS]

33:42.603 --> 33:47.482
I GOT IT.

33:47.650 --> 33:49.234
WHAT?

33:49.402 --> 33:53.864
THE JEALOUSY ANGLE.

33:54.032 --> 33:56.491
YEAH.

33:56.659 --> 34:00.954
[BARKING]

34:01.122 --> 34:02.372
Albert:
IT'S ALL SET, TOBY.

34:02.540 --> 34:04.332
THE WIDOW MUMFORD
IS EXPECTING YOU.

34:04.500 --> 34:06.043
YOU'RE SURE
ABOUT THIS,
ALBERT?

34:06.210 --> 34:08.170
YEAH. SHE'S DYING
TO MEET YOU.

34:08.337 --> 34:10.172
IT'S TRUE, TOBY.
SHE SAW YOU IN CHURCH.

34:10.339 --> 34:11.757
OH, I'LL
SEE YOU LATER.

34:11.924 --> 34:16.428
- BYE, TOBY.
- BYE-BYE. BE GOOD.

34:16.596 --> 34:17.804
SURE HOPE IT WORKS.

34:17.972 --> 34:20.974
IT'LL WORK.
YOU TAKE
MY WORD FOR IT.

34:21.142 --> 34:24.186
SURE WISH I COULD THINK
OF SOMETHING THAT
WOULD WORK WITH JASON.

34:24.353 --> 34:26.730
DO WHAT
I TOLD YOU TO DO
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

34:26.898 --> 34:30.692
PLAY HARD TO GET.
IT'LL WORK LIKE
A CHARM. IGNORE HIM.

34:30.860 --> 34:33.028
I STILL DON'T SEE
HOW TWO PEOPLE
IGNORING EACH OTHER

34:33.196 --> 34:34.863
COULD EVER
GET TOGETHER.

34:35.031 --> 34:37.991
WILL YOU JUST LISTEN
AND DO WHAT I SAY?

34:38.159 --> 34:39.868
I'M LISTENING.

34:40.036 --> 34:43.789
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

34:53.091 --> 34:54.883
OKAY. I'M GOING
TO DO IT, NED.

34:55.051 --> 34:56.384
I'M GOING TO ASK HER
TO THE DANCE.

34:56.552 --> 34:59.262
GREAT. JUST DON'T
LOSE YOUR NERVE.

34:59.430 --> 35:02.766
I WON'T.
HERE I GO.

35:10.900 --> 35:11.858
Jason: LAURA?

35:12.026 --> 35:15.070
NOT WHILE
I'M SHOOTING, JASON.

35:15.238 --> 35:17.572
SORRY.

35:17.740 --> 35:19.908
OH, DARN.

35:20.076 --> 35:21.743
YOUR TURN.

35:21.911 --> 35:22.911
UH, LAURA, I--

35:23.079 --> 35:27.165
ALBERT'S SHOOTING.

35:27.333 --> 35:29.709
WELL, I HAVE TO
ASK YOU A QUESTION.

35:29.877 --> 35:30.919
YOUR TURN.

35:31.087 --> 35:32.671
CAN'T IT WAIT?

35:32.839 --> 35:34.548
WELL, NO.
IT'S IMPORTANT.

35:34.715 --> 35:37.676
NOTHING'S
MORE IMPORTANT
THAN A MARBLE GAME.

35:37.844 --> 35:39.761
HA! GOTCHA.

35:39.929 --> 35:42.180
WELL, IF YOU HAVEN'T
GOT TIME FOR A QUESTION,

35:42.348 --> 35:44.266
I'D JUST LIKE TO SAY...

35:44.433 --> 35:46.268
WELL, THAT...THAT--

35:46.435 --> 35:48.603
THAT WHAT?

35:48.771 --> 35:51.481
THAT YOU'RE
A TOAD FACE.

36:00.408 --> 36:03.076
Woman: I'VE ALWAYS
GOTTEN ALONG WELL
WITH MUSICIANS.

36:03.244 --> 36:05.036
MY FIRST BEAU
WAS A VIOLINIST.

36:05.204 --> 36:07.831
- YES.
- HE HAD SUCH BEAUTIFUL HANDS.

36:07.999 --> 36:08.999
MM-HMM.

36:09.167 --> 36:11.501
I WOULD HAVE MARRIED
HIM, EXCEPT INSANITY

36:11.669 --> 36:13.628
RAN IN HIS FAMILY,
POOR MAN.

36:13.796 --> 36:15.172
HIS MOTHER USED
TO HIDE HIS TROUSERS

36:15.339 --> 36:17.299
SO THAT
HE COULDN'T LEAVE
THE HOUSE, YOU KNOW?

36:17.466 --> 36:18.800
WHAT A PITY.

36:18.968 --> 36:20.135
YES.

36:20.303 --> 36:22.470
Toby: WHY, HERE.
HERE'S A NICE PLACE
RIGHT HERE.

36:22.638 --> 36:24.264
WHAT? OH!

36:24.432 --> 36:25.932
- HERE WE ARE.
- LOVELY.

36:26.100 --> 36:29.311
NOW I'LL GET THE
BLANKET OUT HERE
AND PUT IT DOWN

36:29.478 --> 36:30.896
SO WE'LL BE
COMFORTABLE.

36:31.063 --> 36:34.065
THERE YOU ARE.
AND NOW, MADAM.

36:34.233 --> 36:38.028
OH, THANK YOU,
MR. NOE.

36:41.365 --> 36:44.326
[PLAYING
BEAUTIFUL DREAMER SLOWLY]

36:48.497 --> 36:52.042
[GASPS]

37:07.600 --> 37:12.395
CAN YOU IMAGINE
THAT FOOLISH MAN

37:12.563 --> 37:15.857
GOING WITH
SUCH AN ELDERLY LADY?

37:16.025 --> 37:17.108
[GIGGLING]

37:17.276 --> 37:20.195
I WISH YOU
COULD HAVE KNOWN
HIM, MR. NOE.

37:20.363 --> 37:24.115
HE WAS THE LAST
BEAU I HAD THAT
COURTED ME.

37:24.283 --> 37:27.619
OH, MR. NOE,
MAY I LOOK
AT YOUR HAND?

37:27.787 --> 37:32.165
I CAN TELL A LOT
ABOUT A MAN
FROM HIS HAND.

37:32.333 --> 37:34.542
[SIGHING]

37:34.710 --> 37:38.380
OH! OH, SO SOFT,

37:38.547 --> 37:40.882
SO GENTLE.

37:41.050 --> 37:43.718
SO LOVING.

37:43.886 --> 37:47.222
OH, YOU HAVEN'T
DONE MUCH WORK,
HAVE YOU?

37:47.390 --> 37:50.558
OH, BUT IT'S A VERY
SENSITIVE HAND.

37:50.726 --> 37:54.729
OH, SO TENDER...

37:54.897 --> 37:57.941
YET SO PASSIONATE.

37:58.109 --> 38:00.694
[VOICE SHAKING]
OH, MR. NOE,

38:00.861 --> 38:04.197
KISS ME.

38:04.365 --> 38:06.533
KISS ME NOW!

38:06.701 --> 38:07.993
[TOBY GROANS]

38:08.160 --> 38:13.873
[GASPS]

38:14.041 --> 38:17.502
OH! ANIMALS.

38:17.670 --> 38:19.671
DIDN'T I ALWAYS TELL YOU?

38:19.839 --> 38:22.257
ALL MEN ARE ANIMALS.

38:22.425 --> 38:25.593
[SIGHS]
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

38:31.225 --> 38:35.145
[CRYING]

38:53.539 --> 38:55.665
LAURA.

39:08.137 --> 39:12.724
[BLOWING NOSE LOUDLY]

39:18.439 --> 39:22.108
[CRYING]

39:25.613 --> 39:27.530
THANKS.

39:27.698 --> 39:30.283
I DON'T WANT IT.

39:30.451 --> 39:32.702
OH. I'LL WASH IT

39:32.870 --> 39:37.415
AND GIVE IT BACK TO YOU
IN THE MORNING.

39:37.583 --> 39:41.336
WHY? IT'S YOUR
HANDKERCHIEF.

39:41.504 --> 39:44.881
[SNIFFLING]

39:45.049 --> 39:47.759
I GUESS I REALLY MESSED
UP TODAY, HUH?

39:47.927 --> 39:50.345
YOU SURE DID.

39:55.393 --> 39:58.144
I HOPE NONE OF TOBY'S
BONES ARE BROKEN.

39:58.312 --> 40:01.231
WELL, WHAT ABOUT
MY HEART?

40:01.399 --> 40:04.734
HE CALLED ME
A TOAD FACE.

40:07.863 --> 40:11.074
HE WAS EXAGGERATING.

40:11.242 --> 40:15.954
THANKS A LOT.

40:16.122 --> 40:17.789
LISTEN, DON'T WORRY

40:17.957 --> 40:20.083
ABOUT THE DUMB OLD DANCE.

40:20.251 --> 40:23.128
I'LL DANCE WITH YOU.

40:23.295 --> 40:24.796
THANKS AGAIN.

40:24.964 --> 40:26.714
THERE'S NOTHING
IN THE WORLD MORE FUN

40:26.882 --> 40:30.468
THAN DANCING
WITH YOUR BROTHER.

40:30.636 --> 40:33.555
ALBERT, YOU WANT TO DO
ME A REAL BIG FAVOR?

40:33.722 --> 40:36.015
OH, ANYTHING.

40:36.183 --> 40:39.352
GO TO SLEEP.

40:44.275 --> 40:47.026
GOOD NIGHT, LAURA.

40:47.194 --> 40:49.863
GOOD NIGHT, ALBERT.

40:50.030 --> 40:53.324
[BLOWING NOSE]

41:10.676 --> 41:11.718
HEY, UH--UH...

41:11.886 --> 41:13.636
I--I GOT A PROBLEM,
CHARLES.

41:13.804 --> 41:15.054
I GOT
A REAL PROBLEM.

41:15.222 --> 41:16.764
YOU SEE, AMANDA--
SHE'S THE TYPE

41:16.932 --> 41:18.558
THAT KEEPS IT
ALL INSIDE HER,

41:18.726 --> 41:20.393
NEVER LETS
HER FEELINGS SHOW.

41:20.561 --> 41:22.562
WHILE I--I LET
EVERYTHING SHOW.

41:22.730 --> 41:25.440
AND--AND WE GOT TO
MEET SOMEWHERE
IN THE MIDDLE.

41:25.608 --> 41:27.400
WOULDN'T YOU AGREE?

41:27.568 --> 41:28.651
- TOBY.
- WHAT?

41:28.819 --> 41:30.612
COULD YOU EXCUSE ME
FOR JUST A MINUTE, PLEASE?

41:30.779 --> 41:33.615
OH, I'M SORRY,
CHARLES.

41:41.040 --> 41:43.249
Albert: YOU KNOW,
I'VE BEEN THINKING.

41:43.417 --> 41:44.542
Laura: AND?

41:44.710 --> 41:46.669
I'VE BEEN
THINKING ABOUT
THE JEALOUSY ANGLE.

41:46.837 --> 41:48.630
IT DIDN'T WORK
FOR TOBY.

41:48.797 --> 41:50.256
YEAH, I KNOW.

41:50.424 --> 41:51.508
BUT I DON'T THINK
OLD FOLKS

41:51.675 --> 41:53.384
GET AS JEALOUS
AS YOUNG FOLKS.

41:53.552 --> 41:55.303
IT MAKES THEM
TOO TIRED.

41:55.471 --> 41:58.181
- ALBERT...
- WELL, JUST HEAR ME OUT.

41:58.349 --> 42:00.683
JASON'S BEST FRIEND
IS NED, RIGHT?

42:00.851 --> 42:01.935
YEAH.

42:02.102 --> 42:05.480
WELL, WHAT WOULD
MAKE A FELLOW
MORE JEALOUS

42:05.648 --> 42:07.982
THAN TO SEE
HIS BEST FRIEND
WITH HIS GIRL?

42:08.150 --> 42:09.484
BUT I'M NOT
HIS GIRL.

42:09.652 --> 42:12.445
NO, BUT YOU
WANT TO BE,
DON'T YOU?

42:12.613 --> 42:13.821
WELL, DON'T YOU?

42:13.989 --> 42:14.948
YEAH.

42:15.115 --> 42:17.659
OKAY...NED
LOVES TO EAT.

42:17.826 --> 42:19.160
NOW, WHAT DID YOU
BRING FOR LUNCH?

42:19.328 --> 42:20.787
JUST A PEANUT BUTTER
SANDWICH.

42:20.955 --> 42:22.163
TOBY ATE
EVERYTHING ELSE.

42:22.331 --> 42:24.457
YEAH.
OH, OKAY, THEN.

42:24.625 --> 42:27.877
AT LUNCHTIME,
YOU STRIKE.

42:42.351 --> 42:43.851
AH, MISS COOPER,

42:44.019 --> 42:45.436
I WAS JUST THINKING
ABOUT YOU.

42:45.604 --> 42:47.981
IS THAT RIGHT?

42:48.148 --> 42:49.857
YES. UM...

42:50.025 --> 42:51.025
DO YOU MIND
IF I COME IN AND--

42:51.193 --> 42:54.654
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND,
MRS. INGALLS?

42:54.822 --> 42:57.865
WELL...ACTUALLY,
IT'S ABOUT THE...

42:58.033 --> 42:59.993
THE GENTLEMAN
WHO'S STAYING WITH US.

43:00.160 --> 43:03.246
I BELIEVE YOU KNOW HIM.
MR. TOBY NOE.

43:03.414 --> 43:06.874
DID THAT LUNATIC
PUT YOU UP TO THIS?

43:07.042 --> 43:09.294
NO. THIS WAS MY IDEA,

43:09.461 --> 43:11.379
AND HE'S NOT A LUNATIC.

43:11.547 --> 43:13.381
I DON'T MEAN
TO BE IMPOLITE,

43:13.549 --> 43:14.716
BUT YOU ARE WASTING
YOUR TIME.

43:14.883 --> 43:16.175
I WANT NO PART
OF THAT MAN.

43:16.343 --> 43:18.469
BUT I THINK YOU HAVE
THE WRONG IMPRESSION OF HIM.

43:18.637 --> 43:19.679
OH, NO.

43:19.847 --> 43:21.431
I HAVE THE RIGHT
IMPRESSION.

43:21.599 --> 43:24.183
HE IS IRRESPONSIBLE,
HE IS SLOPPY,

43:24.351 --> 43:25.810
AND I DON'T THINK
HE'S EVER WORKED

43:25.978 --> 43:28.646
A DAY IN HIS LIFE.

43:28.814 --> 43:33.151
WELL, WE ALL HAVE
OUR FAULTS, MISS COOPER.

43:33.319 --> 43:35.778
AND TOBY NOE IS THE MOST
GOOD-NATURED MAN

43:35.946 --> 43:38.114
I BELIEVE
I'VE EVER MET.

43:38.282 --> 43:40.825
WELL, THEN WHY ARE
YOU TRYING TO GIVE
HIM TO ME?

43:40.993 --> 43:44.746
IF HE IS SUCH A PRIZE,
WHY DON'T YOU KEEP HIM
AT YOUR HOUSE?

43:44.913 --> 43:47.415
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S VERY NICE.

43:47.583 --> 43:49.834
HE THINKS THE WORLD
OF YOU.

43:50.002 --> 43:51.127
WELL,
I HAVE GOTTEN ALONG

43:51.295 --> 43:52.712
ALL THESE YEARS
WITHOUT A MAN.

43:52.880 --> 43:55.006
I DON'T NEED MEN.
I DON'T TRUST MEN,

43:55.174 --> 43:57.634
AND THAT
IS THE SIMPLE TRUTH.

43:57.801 --> 43:59.469
I FOUND OUT
THE HARD WAY

43:59.637 --> 44:01.721
WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO OPEN YOUR HEART
TO A MAN.

44:01.889 --> 44:04.557
A BOY BROKE MY HEART
WHEN I WAS YOUNG,
MRS. INGALLS.

44:04.725 --> 44:07.268
HE BROKE IT SO BAD,

44:07.436 --> 44:09.812
SO BAD THAT I CRIED
FOR TWO WHOLE YEARS,

44:09.980 --> 44:12.190
AND I DO NOT NEED
A REPEAT PERFORMANCE.

44:12.358 --> 44:14.525
GOOD DAY,
MRS. INGALLS.

44:17.613 --> 44:20.448
GOOD DAY, MISS COOPER.

45:03.033 --> 45:04.742
HERE COMES LAURA.

45:04.910 --> 45:05.827
SO?

45:05.994 --> 45:07.495
SO, YOU SAID
YOU WANTED
TO APOLOGIZE

45:07.663 --> 45:09.288
FOR CALLING HER
A TOAD FACE.

45:09.456 --> 45:12.041
NOW'S YOUR CHANCE.

45:12.209 --> 45:13.793
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I WILL.

45:19.174 --> 45:22.510
[COYLY]
HI, NED.

45:22.678 --> 45:24.846
HI.

45:25.013 --> 45:29.183
I BROUGHT YOU AN EXTRA
PEANUT BUTTER SANDWICH.

45:29.351 --> 45:32.603
- FOR ME?
- UH-HUH.

45:32.771 --> 45:35.064
HERE.

45:35.232 --> 45:38.693
WELL, THANKS.

45:38.861 --> 45:41.529
MIND IF I SIT
NEXT TO YOU?

45:44.867 --> 45:46.409
GEE, IT SURE IS COZY
LIKE THIS,

45:46.577 --> 45:48.327
ISN'T IT, NED?

45:48.495 --> 45:51.330
IT'S NOT COZY.
IT'S CROWDED.

45:51.498 --> 45:56.794
THANKS
FOR THE SANDWICH.

45:56.962 --> 45:58.004
YOU KNOW, I WAS RIGHT.

45:58.172 --> 46:00.631
YOU ARE A TOAD FACE.

46:10.684 --> 46:13.394
[SIGHS]

46:13.562 --> 46:14.812
Caroline: SO,
IF I WERE YOU,

46:14.980 --> 46:17.231
I'D BE A LITTLE
MORE PATIENT
WITH HER, TOBY.

46:17.399 --> 46:19.317
AFTER ALL,
SHE'S BEEN
WARY OF MEN

46:19.485 --> 46:21.194
FOR A LONG,
LONG TIME.

46:21.361 --> 46:23.237
Toby: SHE DON'T
HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT ME.

46:23.405 --> 46:24.655
I'M THE LOYAL TYPE.

46:24.823 --> 46:26.574
AND IT WOULDN'T
HURT IF YOU CLEANED
YOURSELF UP

46:26.742 --> 46:28.743
A LITTLE BIT EITHER
AND GOT A JOB.

46:28.911 --> 46:30.745
THAT'S WHAT I NEED.
A NEW IMAGE.

46:30.913 --> 46:33.831
OH, CAROLINE,
WOULD YOU GIVE ME
A HAIRCUT?

46:33.999 --> 46:34.999
OF COURSE.

46:35.167 --> 46:37.084
WHAT ABOUT THE
OTHER PART, TOBY?

46:37.252 --> 46:38.669
THE JOB PART?
WE COULD USE A
HAND AT THE MILL.

46:38.837 --> 46:40.421
OH, LET'S NOT GET
CARRIED AWAY, CHARLES.

46:40.589 --> 46:41.714
ONE THING AT A TIME.

46:41.882 --> 46:44.592
UH, CAROLINE,
DO WE HAVE
ANY MORE ROAST?

46:44.760 --> 46:46.344
YES, THE HEAD
AND THE TAIL.

46:46.512 --> 46:48.387
HA HA.

47:02.027 --> 47:04.153
TOBY? COME ON, HURRY
UP. WE'LL BE LATE FOR CHURCH.

47:04.321 --> 47:09.033
Toby: COMING!
I'M COMING!

47:09.201 --> 47:11.702
HEY, YOU LOOK GREAT.
WHERE'D YOU GET
THE SUIT?

47:11.870 --> 47:13.496
THE MERCANTILE.

47:13.664 --> 47:14.831
WELL, HOW DID YOU
PAY FOR IT?

47:14.998 --> 47:17.458
I, UH...
CHARGED IT.

47:17.626 --> 47:18.751
YOU CHARGED IT?
I'M SURPRISED

47:18.919 --> 47:23.506
MRS. OLESON
LET YOU OPEN AN A--

47:23.674 --> 47:27.927
YOU PUT IT
ON MY BILL?

47:28.095 --> 47:29.637
ALL RIGHT,
NOW, TOBY, THIS
IS GOING TO STOP.

47:29.805 --> 47:30.888
YOU'RE GOING TO
GET A JOB.

47:31.056 --> 47:32.390
DON'T YOU YELL AT ME,
CHARLES INGALLS.

47:32.558 --> 47:33.724
IT'S ALL YOUR FAULT
I DON'T HAVE ANY MONEY.

47:33.892 --> 47:35.476
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
MY FAULT?

47:35.644 --> 47:37.311
IF IT HADN'T BEEN
FOR YOU, I'D BE
IN FRISCO RIGHT NOW,

47:37.479 --> 47:40.064
MAKING A BUNDLE.
THERE'S NO GAMBLING
IN THIS ONE-HORSE TOWN.

47:40.232 --> 47:45.528
NOW, COME ON.
WE'RE LATE FOR CHURCH.

47:45.696 --> 47:47.154
OH...

47:47.322 --> 47:51.909
[ORGAN PLAYING SLOWLY]

47:56.206 --> 48:00.126
AMAZING GRACE

48:00.294 --> 48:05.214
HOW SWEET THE SOUND

48:05.382 --> 48:09.635
THAT SAVED A WRETCH

48:09.803 --> 48:13.681
LIKE ME

48:13.849 --> 48:17.935
I ONCE WAS LOST

48:18.103 --> 48:22.523
BUT NOW AM FOUND

48:22.691 --> 48:24.567
WAS BLIND

48:24.735 --> 48:30.364
BUT NOW I SEE

48:30.532 --> 48:34.911
'TWAS GRACE THAT TAUGHT

48:35.078 --> 48:39.206
MY HEART TO FEAR

48:39.374 --> 48:44.795
AND GRACE
MY FEARS RELIEVED

48:47.174 --> 48:51.010
HOW PRECIOUS DID

48:51.178 --> 48:55.389
THAT GRACE APPEAR

48:55.557 --> 48:57.808
THE HOUR

48:57.976 --> 49:03.064
I FIRST BELIEVED

49:09.613 --> 49:10.655
[CONGREGATION SITS DOWN]

49:10.822 --> 49:12.448
I HAVE A FEW
ANNOUNCEMENTS TO MAKE.

49:12.616 --> 49:15.076
THE ANNUAL TOWN DANCE
WILL TAKE PLACE THIS SATURDAY

49:15.243 --> 49:16.911
IN LARSON'S BARN,

49:17.079 --> 49:19.080
AND WE HAVE TWO BIRTHDAYS
THIS WEEK--

49:19.247 --> 49:21.499
FRANK FINNEGAN
ON WEDNESDAY

49:21.667 --> 49:24.335
AND AMANDA COOPER
ON SATURDAY.

49:50.112 --> 49:52.279
Toby: CHARLES!

49:52.447 --> 49:54.115
- CHARLES!
- YEAH?

49:54.282 --> 49:56.242
- I'M GOING TO DO IT.
- YOU'RE GOING TO DO WHAT?

49:56.410 --> 49:57.785
WORK. I'VE GOT TO
MAKE SOME MONEY

49:57.953 --> 49:59.370
TO BUY AMANDA
A BIRTHDAY PRESENT.

49:59.538 --> 50:00.788
HEY, WELL,
THAT'S GREAT, TOBY.

50:00.956 --> 50:02.790
YOU CAN ALSO PAY
FOR YOUR SUIT.
START TOMORROW.

50:02.958 --> 50:05.209
YEAH, YEAH.
SURE.

50:21.226 --> 50:22.601
HOW ARE YOU,
MISS COOPER?

50:22.769 --> 50:26.063
I'M JUST FINE,
THANK YOU, MR. NOE.

50:26.231 --> 50:28.274
OH, FUNNY
OUR STOPPING HERE

50:28.442 --> 50:31.527
IN FRONT OF MY PLACE
OF EMPLOYMENT.

50:31.695 --> 50:33.237
WELL, MR. NOE,
I DIDN'T KNOW

50:33.405 --> 50:34.530
THAT YOU
WERE WORKING.

50:34.698 --> 50:38.075
OH, YES. IT'S HARD
FOR A MAN LIKE MYSELF

50:38.243 --> 50:41.871
TO REMAIN IDLE
FOR LONG.

50:42.039 --> 50:43.247
WOULD YOU ALLOW ME

50:43.415 --> 50:47.043
THE HONOR OF WALKING
YOU HOME?

50:47.210 --> 50:50.963
I'M SURE I'D BE
VERY PLEASED.

50:58.180 --> 51:00.389
[LAUGHING]

51:00.557 --> 51:01.807
Toby: AND HE SAID TO ME,

51:01.975 --> 51:03.517
"DO YOU THINK
IT WILL RAIN?"

51:03.685 --> 51:05.686
AND I SAID,
"IT ALWAYS HAS."

51:05.854 --> 51:06.937
[LAUGHING]

51:07.105 --> 51:08.522
AND I--HE SAID
TO ME AGAIN,

51:08.690 --> 51:10.024
HE SAID, "DO YOU
THINK IT WILL SNOW?"

51:10.192 --> 51:13.277
I SAID,
"IT ALWAYS HAS."

51:13.445 --> 51:16.572
OH, MR. NOE,
YOU ARE SO FUNNY.

51:16.740 --> 51:19.033
I REALLY ENJOY
YOUR SENSE OF HUMOR.

51:19.201 --> 51:21.035
OH, I'M GLAD.
AND YOU...

51:21.203 --> 51:22.703
YOU WOULD MAKE ME
SO HAPPY

51:22.871 --> 51:25.790
IF YOU WOULD
CALL ME TOBY.

51:25.957 --> 51:28.501
ALL RIGHT.
TOBY IT IS.

51:28.668 --> 51:31.837
HA HA HA.
THANK YOU, AMANDA.

51:32.005 --> 51:34.256
[LAUGHING NERVOUSLY]

51:34.424 --> 51:36.175
AH, WELL, UH,
I WANT TO THANK YOU

51:36.343 --> 51:39.678
FOR A DELIGHTFUL
AFTERNOON.

51:39.846 --> 51:42.807
OH, IT WAS MY PLEASURE.

51:42.974 --> 51:44.892
WOULD YOU ALLOW ME
TO ESCORT YOU

51:45.060 --> 51:48.395
TO THE DANCE
SATURDAY NIGHT?

51:48.563 --> 51:49.897
OH, YES.

51:50.065 --> 51:51.190
AND, UM...

51:51.358 --> 51:55.778
WOULD YOU LIKE TO COME
TO DINNER ON THURSDAY?

51:55.946 --> 51:57.780
TRY AND STOP ME.

51:57.948 --> 51:59.573
WHAT TIME
SHALL I COME?

51:59.741 --> 52:02.409
7:00.

52:21.263 --> 52:24.056
TILL THURSDAY,

52:24.224 --> 52:26.809
MY SOUTHERN ROSE.

53:19.571 --> 53:23.324
[SAW BUZZING]

53:34.669 --> 53:39.465
[GARVEY LAUGHING]

53:42.761 --> 53:45.554
Toby: HMM...
THAT'S PRETTY.

53:45.722 --> 53:47.681
HMM, THAT'S PRETTY.

53:47.849 --> 53:49.892
THAT'S PRETTY, TOO.

53:50.060 --> 53:51.602
SO'S THAT.

53:51.770 --> 53:54.438
WELL, TOBY...

53:54.606 --> 53:56.190
WHAT SHALL IT BE?

53:56.358 --> 53:58.150
WELL,
THERE ARE SO MANY
TO CHOOSE FROM,

53:58.318 --> 54:00.778
I--I CAN'T
MAKE UP MY MIND.

54:00.946 --> 54:03.197
WHICH ONE WOULD
YOUR MISSIS LIKE?

54:03.365 --> 54:05.532
- THE MOST EXPENSIVE ONE.
- HA HA HA.

54:05.700 --> 54:11.205
BUT IF YOU ASK ME,
THIS IS THE PRETTIEST ONE.

54:11.373 --> 54:12.873
I THINK
YOU'RE RIGHT.

54:13.041 --> 54:14.291
I'LL TAKE IT.

54:14.459 --> 54:17.044
GOOD. I'VE GOT
A LOVELY BOX FOR YOU.

54:17.212 --> 54:19.129
IT'S SOMEWHERE
IN THE STOREROOM.
I'LL GET IT.

54:19.297 --> 54:21.215
OH, THANKS, NELS.

54:21.383 --> 54:23.676
BOY, I HOPE
SHE LIKES IT.

54:23.843 --> 54:26.387
[BELL RINGS]

54:29.266 --> 54:31.058
UHH!

54:44.364 --> 54:45.614
YOO-HOO!

54:45.782 --> 54:47.116
ANYBODY HERE?

54:47.284 --> 54:48.575
Nels: I'LL BE
RIGHT THERE!

54:48.743 --> 54:53.247
OH, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'LL JUST LOOK AROUND.

54:53.415 --> 54:55.082
BLANKETS...

54:55.250 --> 54:57.960
OOH! DRESSES!

54:58.128 --> 55:02.381
GREEN DOESN'T
BECOME YOUR BEAUTY.

55:02.549 --> 55:06.885
OH! OOH!

55:07.053 --> 55:11.098
OH, MR. NOE!
PEEK-A-BOO!

55:11.266 --> 55:12.433
YOU DEVIL, YOU.

55:12.600 --> 55:16.312
OH, SNEAKING IN HERE
TO SURPRISE ME.

55:16.479 --> 55:18.230
NO, I WASN'T
SNEAKING IN TO...I--

55:18.398 --> 55:19.440
HAVE YOU BEEN THINKING

55:19.607 --> 55:21.734
ABOUT OUR PICNIC
THE OTHER DAY?

55:21.901 --> 55:24.862
EVERY TIME I TOUCH MY RIBS.
I THINK THEY'RE BROKEN.

55:25.030 --> 55:26.822
OH, I'M SO SORRY
ABOUT THAT,

55:26.990 --> 55:30.617
BUT YOU
REMINDED ME SO MUCH
OF MY LATE HUSBAND.

55:30.785 --> 55:31.827
[LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]

55:31.995 --> 55:33.370
NOW I KNOW HOW HE DIED.

55:33.538 --> 55:38.459
[GIGGLING] OH...

55:38.626 --> 55:42.588
BUT YOU'RE ALIVE.

55:42.756 --> 55:44.631
HEH HEH.

55:44.799 --> 55:46.425
HERE WE GO, TOBY.

55:46.593 --> 55:48.969
- OH!
- THANKS, NELS.

55:49.137 --> 55:50.596
SETS IT OFF JUST RIGHT,
DOESN'T IT?

55:50.764 --> 55:56.643
OH, MR. NOE!
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE!

55:56.811 --> 55:58.312
I--I DIDN'T!

55:58.480 --> 56:00.898
OH, I KNOW YOU WANTED
TO SURPRISE ME,

56:01.066 --> 56:03.525
BUT, OH...

56:03.693 --> 56:04.985
KISS ME!

56:05.153 --> 56:07.321
KISS ME NOW!

56:07.489 --> 56:09.281
Nels: WHOA!

56:25.006 --> 56:29.635
AMANDA,
THIS IS DELICIOUS.

56:29.803 --> 56:31.261
YOU MEAN IT, TOBY?

56:31.429 --> 56:33.472
OF COURSE I MEAN IT.

56:33.640 --> 56:36.683
FOOD IS IMPORTANT
TO ME.

56:36.851 --> 56:37.851
MY FATHER ALWAYS SAID,

56:38.019 --> 56:43.065
"SON, COOKING IS HALF
OF A MARRIAGE."

56:53.993 --> 56:55.619
OH...

57:02.001 --> 57:07.131
AMANDA, I HAVE
A SURPRISE FOR YOU.

57:07.298 --> 57:12.886
I WAS...GOING
TO GIVE IT TO YOU
ON YOUR BIRTHDAY,

57:13.054 --> 57:15.931
BUT HERE.

57:29.028 --> 57:30.446
OPEN IT.

57:41.082 --> 57:43.584
IT'S, UM...

57:43.751 --> 57:46.044
IT'S VERY PRETTY.

57:46.212 --> 57:48.505
IT'S MY WAY OF SAYING

57:48.673 --> 57:52.634
I'VE BEEN LOOKING
FOR YOU ALL MY LIFE.

57:56.764 --> 57:58.015
TOBY, UM...

57:58.183 --> 58:00.350
I WANT YOU
TO GO HOME NOW.

58:00.518 --> 58:03.937
HOME?

58:04.105 --> 58:05.272
WHY?

58:05.440 --> 58:07.983
I JUST WANT YOU
TO GO HOME,
THAT'S ALL.

58:08.151 --> 58:11.069
AMANDA, WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

58:11.237 --> 58:13.822
I HAVE BEEN
THINKING ABOUT THIS
FOR A LONG TIME,

58:13.990 --> 58:16.617
AND WE ARE JUST
TOO DIFFERENT,

58:16.784 --> 58:19.119
YOU AND I.

58:19.287 --> 58:20.454
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU MEAN.

58:20.622 --> 58:22.331
YOU--YOU NEED ME.

58:22.499 --> 58:25.125
I DON'T NEED ANYONE.

58:25.293 --> 58:28.128
TOBY, YOU HAVE
BEEN A TRAMP
MOST OF YOUR LIFE.

58:28.296 --> 58:29.755
WHY, I COULD NEVER
SETTLE DOWN

58:29.923 --> 58:31.423
WITH ANYONE LIKE
THAT. NEVER!

58:31.591 --> 58:33.842
BUT I'M WORKING NOW,
AND I'M WILLING TO...

58:34.010 --> 58:36.261
TO WORK ALL THE REST
OF MY DAYS.

58:36.429 --> 58:37.638
IT JUST
WOULDN'T WORK.

58:37.805 --> 58:40.224
NOW, THERE ARE
A MILLION REASONS.

58:40.391 --> 58:43.310
BUT...WELL,
NAME ONE.

58:43.478 --> 58:46.647
UP TILL NOW,
YOU'RE TALKING NONSENSE.

58:46.814 --> 58:47.814
ALL RIGHT.

58:47.982 --> 58:49.107
I'M GOING TO
SAY THIS,

58:49.275 --> 58:52.361
AND YOU ARE
FORCING ME TO.

58:52.529 --> 58:55.531
TOBY, YOU ARE
TOO OLD FOR ME.

58:55.698 --> 58:57.282
I MEAN IT,
TOO OLD.

58:57.450 --> 58:59.368
AND, UM...

58:59.536 --> 59:03.205
UH, ANYWAY,
UH, THE MAN
I HAD IN MIND

59:03.373 --> 59:08.377
IS, UM, MUCH
BETTER LOOKING
THAN YOU ARE.

59:12.757 --> 59:15.676
I AM TRULY SORRY

59:15.843 --> 59:21.932
THAT IT HAS TO
END LIKE THIS.

59:46.958 --> 59:49.418
HERE'S YOUR BROACH.

59:54.090 --> 59:56.883
YOU KEEP IT.

59:57.051 --> 1:00:00.387
IT WOULDN'T LOOK GOOD
ON ME ANYWAY.

1:00:07.437 --> 1:00:10.272
[DOOR CLOSES]

1:00:13.776 --> 1:00:17.988
[CRYING]

1:00:23.202 --> 1:00:26.496
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT WENT WRONG.

1:00:26.664 --> 1:00:29.916
WHAT?

1:00:30.084 --> 1:00:32.836
I KNOW SHE LIKED ME.

1:00:33.004 --> 1:00:35.964
I DIDN'T DREAM
THAT WHOLE AFTERNOON.

1:00:36.132 --> 1:00:39.551
DID I?

1:00:39.719 --> 1:00:41.553
WOMEN.

1:00:41.721 --> 1:00:46.099
WOMEN.
WHAT DO THEY WANT?

1:00:46.267 --> 1:00:48.393
YOU CAN'T LIVE
WITH THEM,

1:00:48.561 --> 1:00:52.981
YOU CAN'T LIVE
WITHOUT THEM.

1:00:53.149 --> 1:00:55.025
I'M SORRY.

1:00:55.193 --> 1:00:58.779
I DON'T KNOW WHY
I'M TELLING YOU
ALL MY TROUBLES.

1:00:58.946 --> 1:01:03.408
HA HA HA.
I'LL GET YOU A DRINK.

1:01:30.353 --> 1:01:34.231
[SLURRED SPEECH]
THEN SHE TOLD ME
I WAS TOO OLD

1:01:34.399 --> 1:01:37.484
AND THAT
I WAS A TRAMP.

1:01:37.652 --> 1:01:41.113
I WORKED MY BUTT OFF
TO GET THAT BROACH FOR HER,

1:01:41.280 --> 1:01:45.951
AND SHE CALLED ME A TRAMP.

1:01:46.119 --> 1:01:48.328
AND I TOOK IT.

1:01:48.496 --> 1:01:53.166
I JUST SAT THERE
AND TOOK IT.

1:01:53.334 --> 1:01:57.087
WELL, I'M JUST GOING
TO TELL HER WHAT'S WHAT.

1:01:59.549 --> 1:02:01.341
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

1:02:01.509 --> 1:02:04.678
Toby, yelling:
OPEN UP!
LET ME IN!

1:02:04.846 --> 1:02:06.930
OPEN UP!
OPEN UP!

1:02:07.098 --> 1:02:08.974
GO HOME.
YOU HEAR ME?

1:02:09.142 --> 1:02:10.600
I HAVE SOMETHING
TO SAY!

1:02:10.768 --> 1:02:13.770
IF YOU DON'T OPEN UP,
I'LL YELL SO LOUD,

1:02:13.938 --> 1:02:18.859
THE WHOLE TOWN
WILL HEAR.

1:02:19.026 --> 1:02:20.110
ALL RIGHT.

1:02:20.278 --> 1:02:22.154
SPEAK YOUR PIECE.
I NEED MY SLEEP.

1:02:22.321 --> 1:02:25.031
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL SPEAK MY PIECE.

1:02:25.199 --> 1:02:27.451
FIRST OF ALL,
YOU'RE OLDER THAN I AM.

1:02:27.618 --> 1:02:29.828
ANYONE CAN SEE THAT.

1:02:29.996 --> 1:02:31.496
I'M DOING YOU
THE FAVOR.

1:02:31.664 --> 1:02:32.622
SECOND OF ALL,

1:02:32.790 --> 1:02:34.458
I'M BETTER LOOKING
THAN YOU.

1:02:34.625 --> 1:02:37.794
DON'T YOU DARE
CALL ME UGLY.

1:02:37.962 --> 1:02:40.380
I NEVER SAID THAT.

1:02:40.548 --> 1:02:41.882
THAT'S ALL
A LOT OF LIES.

1:02:42.049 --> 1:02:43.091
NONE OF THAT
IS THE REAL REASON

1:02:43.259 --> 1:02:45.594
WHY YOU'RE TRYING
TO BREAK US UP.

1:02:45.762 --> 1:02:47.095
YOU'RE AFRAID
OF FEELINGS.

1:02:47.263 --> 1:02:48.346
YOU'RE AFRAID
OF LIVING.

1:02:48.514 --> 1:02:51.433
YOU'RE AFRAID
OF NEEDING ME.

1:02:51.601 --> 1:02:52.976
THAT IS RIDICULOUS.

1:02:53.144 --> 1:02:55.812
NOT SO RIDICULOUS
AS TALKING
TO THAT DUMB CAT.

1:02:55.980 --> 1:03:00.066
[MEOW]

1:03:00.234 --> 1:03:03.195
YOU HAVE SAID YOUR PIECE.
YOU CAN GO NOW.

1:03:28.638 --> 1:03:32.182
I HAD LOVED YOU.

1:03:37.605 --> 1:03:39.105
SPEND THE REST
OF YOUR LIFE

1:03:39.273 --> 1:03:43.860
TALKING
TO THAT DUMB CAT.

1:04:10.972 --> 1:04:13.932
Charles: EVERY SUBJECT
ISN'T MY FAVORITE SUBJECT.

1:04:14.100 --> 1:04:18.812
YOU GOT TO WORK
AT IT.

1:04:18.980 --> 1:04:20.772
- GOOD MORNING, TOBY.
- MORNING.

1:04:20.940 --> 1:04:22.649
I'LL GET
YOUR BREAKFAST
FOR YOU.

1:04:22.817 --> 1:04:23.984
OH, NO, THANK YOU,
CAROLINE.

1:04:24.151 --> 1:04:27.279
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

1:04:35.162 --> 1:04:37.789
CHARLES,
I'D APPRECIATE IT

1:04:37.957 --> 1:04:42.294
IF YOU'D TAKE ME
TO THE TRAIN STATION
TODAY.

1:04:44.839 --> 1:04:47.173
SURE, IF THAT'S
WHAT YOU WANT, TOBY.

1:04:47.341 --> 1:04:49.426
TOBY, PLEASE
DON'T GO.

1:04:49.594 --> 1:04:52.345
SHE WAS MEAN TO YOU.
WE WEREN'T.

1:04:52.513 --> 1:04:54.681
AND THE DANCE
IS TONIGHT.

1:04:54.849 --> 1:04:59.352
WHO'S GOING TO PLAY
THE ACCORDION?

1:04:59.520 --> 1:05:01.021
PLEASE, TOBY.

1:05:01.188 --> 1:05:03.398
STAY WITH US,
PLEASE.

1:05:07.612 --> 1:05:09.529
ALL RIGHT.

1:05:09.697 --> 1:05:12.490
I'LL GO THE FIRST THING
IN THE MORNING.

1:05:24.170 --> 1:05:25.879
HALF-PINT?

1:05:26.047 --> 1:05:28.214
HEY, COME ON.
EVERYBODY'S READY.

1:05:28.382 --> 1:05:30.216
DO I HAVE TO GO, PA?

1:05:30.384 --> 1:05:31.635
NOW, COME ON.
ONCE YOU GET THERE,

1:05:31.802 --> 1:05:33.094
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
A GOOD TIME.

1:05:33.262 --> 1:05:35.764
CAN'T I JUST STAY HOME
AND TAKE CARE OF BABY GRACE?

1:05:35.932 --> 1:05:38.516
MRS. TERHUNE IS
GOING TO TAKE CARE
OF BABY GRACE.

1:05:38.684 --> 1:05:40.060
AND YOU TOLD ME
YOURSELF

1:05:40.227 --> 1:05:42.062
THERE'S GOING TO BE
A LOT OF GIRLS THERE
WITHOUT BEAUS.

1:05:42.229 --> 1:05:43.438
YEAH, NELLIE OLESON.

1:05:43.606 --> 1:05:45.649
AND THE ONLY REASON
WHY BOYS WILL ASK HER
TO DANCE

1:05:45.816 --> 1:05:50.070
IS BECAUSE SHE BRINGS
A 10-POUND BAG OF CANDY
WITH HER.

1:05:50.237 --> 1:05:51.905
LOTS OF BOYS
ARE GOING TO
ASK YOU TO DANCE,

1:05:52.073 --> 1:05:53.323
AND BESIDES, I WANT
TO HAVE A DANCE

1:05:53.491 --> 1:05:57.369
WITH MY BEST
GIRL, TOO.

1:05:57.536 --> 1:06:00.622
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL BE RIGHT DOWN.

1:06:00.790 --> 1:06:02.248
THAT'S MY GIRL.

1:06:07.588 --> 1:06:10.715
WHAT A FUN NIGHT.

1:06:10.883 --> 1:06:14.219
I GET TO DANCE
WITH MY BROTHER
AND MY PA.

1:06:14.387 --> 1:06:18.264
[ACCORDION PLAYING]

1:07:42.933 --> 1:07:44.350
[MUSIC PLAYING IN DISTANCE]

1:07:44.518 --> 1:07:46.061
ISN'T THIS NICE,
PERCY?

1:07:46.228 --> 1:07:49.355
JUST YOU AND ME
ON MY BIRTHDAY.

1:07:49.523 --> 1:07:51.983
[MEOW]

1:07:52.151 --> 1:07:54.402
THEY PLAY THAT MUSIC
SO LOUD, IT...

1:07:54.570 --> 1:07:57.072
IT WOULD WAKE THE DEAD.

1:07:57.239 --> 1:08:00.408
PROBABLY
THAT TOBY NOE'S FAULT.

1:08:00.576 --> 1:08:02.827
HE'S SO OLD,
HE DIDN'T KNOW HE'S DEAF.

1:08:02.995 --> 1:08:07.499
HE CAN'T EVEN HEAR IT.

1:08:07.666 --> 1:08:11.169
STOP PLAYING
WITH THAT BROACH.

1:08:11.337 --> 1:08:14.297
DID YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

1:08:14.465 --> 1:08:16.174
[MEOW]

1:08:16.342 --> 1:08:18.593
WELL, OF COURSE YOU DIDN'T.

1:08:18.761 --> 1:08:20.970
YOU'RE A CAT.

1:08:21.138 --> 1:08:24.015
I'M TALKING TO A CAT.

1:08:24.183 --> 1:08:29.270
I AM TALKING TO A CAT!

1:08:29.438 --> 1:08:31.481
THAT MAN LOVES ME,

1:08:31.649 --> 1:08:35.944
AND I'M TALKING TO A CAT.

1:08:41.617 --> 1:08:44.786
[LIVELY SONG PLAYING]

1:09:46.473 --> 1:09:49.642
[APPLAUSE]

1:10:03.657 --> 1:10:04.824
BEAUTIFUL DREAMER.

1:10:04.992 --> 1:10:07.994
[PLAYING BEAUTIFUL DREAMER]

1:11:17.773 --> 1:11:21.234
LAURA?

1:11:21.402 --> 1:11:26.322
I'M SORRY I CALLED YOU
A TOAD FACE.

1:11:26.490 --> 1:11:31.703
I'M SORRY I DIDN'T
LISTEN TO YOUR QUESTION.

1:11:31.870 --> 1:11:34.122
CAN I HAVE THIS DANCE?
